From the above information, the most information can be drawn from the fifth module. This makes sense as it takes into account every aspect of the students application that we have. We will next make a new data frame (df_pred) adding the predictions that can be made with this module. Here is a list of the names of the columns in this data frame.

## [1] "admit" "gre"   "gpa"   "rank"  "pred"

Notice the new column titled pred. This is a prediction on a 0-1 scale on an applicants chances at getting into their respective graduate program.

Now, we can use graphs to further visualize and analyze the data

GPAs Impact

This graph shows that the higher a students GPA is, the better chance they have at getting into graduate school.

Rank and GPA Impact

If we separate data in the above graph based on the ranking of the undergraduate institutions, we see more information.

The better ranked their undergraduate program, the more likely they are to get in. Below is the raw data showing this prediction.

## 
## Call:
## glm(formula = admit ~ rank, data = df)

The p-value is severely less than .05 indicating a significant relationship between admission and the ranking of the undergraduate program.

GRE Impact

Next, we will run the same graph as above but showcasing GREs impact on the students chances at being admitted

ggplot(df_pred,aes(x=gre,y=pred,color=factor(rank))) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm") +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x="GRE",y="Prediction",title = "GPA's Affect on Admission",color="Rank")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Again, we can make the same conclusions that the higher ones GRE scores the better their chances at getting into their graduate program. We again see the same impact that rank of undergraduate instution had when looking at GPA applies here too.

Conclusions

By analyzing the data above, we see that GPA, GRE, and the rank of undergraduate instituion all have affect on a students chance of getting admitted to their graduate program. The higher ones GRE, GPA, and undergraduate instition ranking, the higher their chances of getting into their program.
